data.title: Princess Caroline — Event's Blog — UFO No More
data.text:
On Tuesday, the Olympic Torch Relay took place in Monaco. Prince Albert and Princess Charlene were torchbearers and they were joined by their children as well as by Princess Caroline and Pierre and Beatrice Casiraghi.

On Tuesday, Prince Albert received the insignia of Commander of the Order of Agricultural Merit from French President Emmanuel Macron. Princess Charlene, Prince Jacques, Princess Gabriella, and Princess Caroline attended the ceremony.

On Saturday, members of the Monégasque Princely Family attended the 2024 Rose Ball benefitting the Princess Grace Foundation. This year’s theme was “Disco”.

On Sunday evening, Prince Albert, Princess Charlene, and Princess Caroline attended the official National Day Gala. They were joined by Princess Alexandra.

On Saturday, the Monegasque Princely Family will celebrate Monaco’s National Day. Ahead of the main day of celebrations, Prince Albert awarded several orders to Monegasque citizens and he was joined by members of the Princely family.

On Wednesday, Prince Albert and Princess Charlene carried out the recommissioning of the two saluting cannons dating from 1881. Princess Caroline, Princess Stéphanie, and Louis Ducruet also attended the ceremony.

On Friday, Prince Albert, Princess Charlene, Princess Caroline, Princess Stéphanie, Andrea Casiraghi, Charlotte Casiraghi, Louis Ducruet, and Camille Gottlieb attended a tribute ceremony to Prince Rainier III hosted by the National Council.

On Tuesday evening, members of the Monégasque Princely Family attended the screening of the "Rainier III par Lui-même" documentary film.

On Saturday, Prince Albert, Princess Caroline, Princess Stéphanie, Louis Ducruet, and Camille Gottlieb attended the naming ceremony of the new Lycée Rainier III.

On Saturday, Prince Albert, Princess Charlene, Prince Jacques, Princess Gabriella, Princess Caroline, and Princess Stéphanie opened the village of the Grimaldi Historic Sites of Monaco.

On Wednesday, the Monégasque Princely Family attended a mass in memory of Prince Rainier III. Prince Rainier III died on 6 April 2005 and 2023 also marks the 100th anniversary of his birth.

On Saturday, members of the Monégasque Princely Family attended the 2023 Rose Ball benefitting the Princess Grace Foundation.

Welcome to this week’s Royal Recap where we’ll take a look at the events we weren’t able to cover fully this week!

On Saturday, the Monégasque Princely Family will celebrate Monaco’s National Day. Ahead of the main day of celebrations, Prince Albert awarded several orders to Monegasque citizens and he was joined by members of the Princely family.
